The &quot;default&quot; field at avro schema is used for schema evolution cases. See http://avro.apache.org/docs/current/spec.html#Schema+Resolution for its rules.

The default value is not used when serializing (writing) the data. It is used when desalinizing (reading) avro data, which was produced with schema which lack the field.

e.g. if we have data which was produced with this schema:

    {
        &quot;type&quot;:&quot;record&quot;,
        &quot;name&quot;:&quot;Product&quot;,
        &quot;fields&quot;:[
             {&quot;name&quot;:&quot;product_id&quot;,&quot;type&quot;: &quot;long&quot;}
        ]
     } 

and we want to read it (resolve it) using extended schema which contains also product_name field like this:

    {
        &quot;type&quot;:&quot;record&quot;,
        &quot;name&quot;:&quot;Product&quot;,
        &quot;fields&quot;:[
            {&quot;name&quot;:&quot;product_id&quot;,&quot;type&quot;: &quot;long&quot;},
            {&quot;name&quot;:&quot;product_name&quot;,&quot;type&quot;: &quot;string&quot;,&quot;default&quot;:&quot;old product data&quot;},
        ]
    } 

The default value will be used to set a value for the field &#39;product_name&#39; which is missing from the data, as the data was written using the first schema.

